{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "They had a total mass of 106 kg and were equipped with one 3-in.",
    "photomultiplier tube (PMT) at each of the two ends, enabling the detection of scintillation light.",
    "Each crystal was housed within a copper encapsulation.",
    "The setup featured eight such encapsulations submerged in a 2200 L volume of LAB-based liquid scintillator (LS), which served as an active veto system [61].",
    "An acrylic box contained the LS, with eighteen PMTs attached to its walls for scintillation light detection, respectively."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "The setup featured eight such encapsulations submerged in a 2200 L volume of LAB-based liquid scintillator (LS), which served as an active veto system [61]."
  ]
